```

"test string" doesn't get picked up by makemessages.

I know that it says in the docs that nose isn't properly tested with hypothesis, but I don't think it's implied strongly enough. The ability in nose to yield functions that assert things (eg. for testing a range of data with the same test) was one of the reasons I started using nose, however it doesn't appear that Hypothesis picks on up failing asserts inside of yields. So perhaps this could either be fixed, or it could be expressly mentioned in the compatibility section of the docs, because this yeild syntax seems to be a big selling point of nose.

Here's the code to reproduce it:

```python
@given(just(''))
def test_shouldfail(s):
    for _ in range(10):
        assert False
```

This fails as expected. However:

```python
def alwaysfails(s)
    assert False
@given(just(''))
def test_shouldfail(s):
    for _ in range(10):
        yield alwaysfail, s
```

Should fail but doesn't.

