This might not be the correct place to ask this however python markdown math fails to render `\label` and `\ref`.

A simple example given by [Mathjax](http://docs.mathjax.org/en/latest/tex.html) is,

```latex
In equation \eqref{eq:sample}, we find the value of an
interesting integral:

\begin{equation}
  \int_0^\infty \frac{x^3}{e^x-1}\,dx = \frac{\pi^4}{15}
  \label{eq:sample}
\end{equation}
````
Interestingly `\tag` works perfectly but it's not so useful to me when I want to reference.

As a motivation my idea of markdown math is to be able to render everything seen in the [Feynman Lectures](http://www.feynmanlectures.caltech.edu/III_02.html). The use of MathJax here simple but amazing which some features are missing in every Markdown math extension I've used so far.

